matchDetail.tossMessage: New Zealand Women won the toss and elected to bowl.

relatedVideos.summary: Outswinger, outswinger, straight one! Some classic fast-bowling in a terrific three-ball sequence from Ellyse Perry saw the end of Lauren Down to have Australia on top in the first ODI at the WACA
relatedVideos.title: How to set up a batter, by Ellyse Perry

relatedVideos.summary: White Ferns star bats Sophie Devine and Suzie Bates were both back in the sheds early as Australia's opening bowlers struck twice early with the new ball in the first ODI at the WACA
relatedVideos.title: NZ in early strife as Devine, Bates depart

relatedVideos.summary: Elevated to the top of the Australian order for the first ODI against New Zealand, former skipper Rachael Haynes struck an important 67 as wickets tumbled around her at the WACA
relatedVideos.title: Promoted Haynes plays lone hand

relatedVideos.summary: After a ball of the summer contender from Lea Tahuhu to remove Alyssa Healy, Meg Lanning departed courtesy of a superb catch from Amy Satterthwaite to hand Rosemary Mair a debut wicket in the first ODI at the WACA
relatedVideos.title: Kiwis on fire early as Healy, Lanning exit

relatedVideos.summary: Australia and New Zealand have finalised their preparations ahead of the first match in the three-game ODI series at the WACA Ground in Perth on Friday
relatedVideos.title: Rivals ready for trans-Tasman series

relatedVideos.summary: Meg Lanning and Amy Satterthwaite are considering including an extra quick bowler for the opening match of the ODI series between Australia and New Zealand
relatedVideos.title: Skippers expecting pace in Perth wicket

relatedVideos.summary: Meg Lanning analyses two of Australia's biggest dangers in the Commonwealth Bank ODI series - New Zealand's Suzie Bates and Sophie Devine
relatedVideos.title: Aussie skipper wary of dynamic Kiwi duo

relatedVideos.summary: After a heavy dose of T20 cricket this summer, Australia are now ready for some 50-over action against New Zealand in Perth, Adelaide and Melbourne.
relatedVideos.title: Aussies ready for return of the Kiwis

relatedVideos.summary: Aussie skipper Meg Lanning drills into Alyssa Healy's unbelievable run of form ahead of the pair reuniting to take on New Zealand on Friday
relatedVideos.title: Lanning's insight into Healy purple patch

matchWrapArticle.title: LIVE: Aussies strike as Kiwis chase 242
